This paper discusses the use of evolutionary computation methods in solving automatic program synthesis problems, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on comparing and combining two parent selection methods, lexicase selection and novelty search, which are commonly used in the field of evolutionary computation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the effects of these methods on population diversity and long-term problem solving performance, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
